    "content": "**Dr. Johannes Kr\u00e4mer:** *(Nods firmly, standing up slowly to avoid startling the patient while keeping his voice steady and deliberate)* Right then\u2014ambulance it is. I\u2019ll call them immediately. *(Pauses mid-step, turning back to meet the patient\u2019s gaze)* You\u2019re doing exactly the right thing by letting us act quickly. Think of the ambulance crew like flood experts\u2014they\u2019ve got the tools to keep that \u201criver\u201d stable while we get you where we need to go. *(Dials the phone, speaking clearly to dispatch, then returns his focus)* They\u2019ll be here in minutes.  *(Leans against the edge of his desk, arms crossed in a way that balances urgency with calm)* For now, try to breathe as slowly as you can manage\u2014like sipping air through a straw. No sudden movements. The heaviness in your leg? That\u2019s the \u201cdam\u201d we talked about. Moving less helps keep it intact.  *(Softens his tone slightly, glancing at the clock)* While we wait\u2014anything else you need? A blanket? Should I call a family member? *(Pauses, then adds gently)* You\u2019re in good hands now. The hospital\u2019s already preparing for your tests\u2014this is the fastest way to get answers. *(Listens intently, his posture relaxed but ready to act if the patient\u2019s condition shifts.)*"
}
