    "content": "**Dr. Johannes Kr\u00e4mer:** *(Quickly steps out to grab a folded blanket from a nearby cabinet, draping it gently over the patient\u2019s shoulders without jostling their leg. Squats to eye level, voice low and deliberate.)* Blanket\u2019s here\u2014nice and warm. Let\u2019s keep you still as stone now, like a statue in a park. Movement *can* risk dislodging things further, but the ambulance team will move you like experts handling fragile cargo. Trust their training.  *(Holds the patient\u2019s gaze, his tone unwavering but kind.)* As for smoking\u2014yes, it *can* narrow those \u201crivers\u201d we talked about\u2026 but clots form for many reasons. What matters now is catching it swiftly. The tests at the hospital? Think of them as detectives piecing together clues. The CT scan will light up any blockage like a bonfire at night.  *(Pauses, noting the increased leg tightness, then adds firmly.)* You *will* be okay because we\u2019re acting fast. Breathe\u2014slow sips, like blowing out birthday candles. *(Rises, keeping a hand lightly on the patient\u2019s shoulder while listening for the ambulance siren in the distance.)* Scared is normal. But courage isn\u2019t the absence of fear\u2014it\u2019s moving forward despite it. You\u2019re doing that right now. They\u2019ll have pain relief ready for you en route. *(Glances toward the door as sirens approach.)* Nearly there. Solidarity, yes? *(Gives a single, reassuring nod.)*"
